<title>Deployment (DevOps</title>
<h1>FOAM Deployment Features</h1>
<p>FOAM has support for building, uploading, and install a complete application.</p>

<h2>Building for deployment</h2>
<p>Deployment builds generate a tar ball.</p>
<code>node foam3/tools/build.js -ckJyour_deployment_directories,../foam/deployment/https</code>

<h2>Uploading / Installing</h2>
<p>Once a tar ball is prepared, it can be uploaded and the application installed</p>
<code>foam3/tools/bin/install_remote.sh -Hhostname</code>
<p>This will upload and install</p>
<p>Additional (most common) flags for install_remote.sh:
<ul>
<li><b>-Uname</b> User name to create and run application under</li>
<li><b>-Yid</b> User ID to create User with</li>
<li><b>-Btrue|false</b> Controls backup of previous version during install. Defaults to true</li>
</ul>
</p>

<h2>SSH Considerations</h2>
<p><b>NOTE</b> The upload and install process assume the uploader's ssh key is installed on the remote host, and that ssh has been configured for no-password logins.</p>
<p><b>TODO:</b> creating ssh key pair, uploading, no-password login configuration</p>

<h2>JVM Memory</h2>
<p>JVM Memory configuration defaults to <b>-Xms2048m</b> and <b>-Xmx4096</b>.<br/>
These properties can be overridden after first deployment by adding them to:
<code>/opt/name/conf/shrc.custom</code>
<code>
#!/bin/bash
  JAVA_OPTS="${JAVA_OPTS} -Xmx8000m"
</code>
</p>

<h2>JVM Other Defaults and Tuning</h2>
Other JVM options, such as Garbage Collection, are defined in:
<code>/opt/name/etc/shrc.local</code>
To override set in conf/shrc.local (see above).

